<div id="Idea_3600"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3600-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3600">Too many laws and too complex&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/6746-4049">farseer2002</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">4 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Our laws are too long, too complex and too unreadable.<br/><br/>The grand total of all federal laws should be limited such that a single human being can read the entire body of federal law in five years spending no more than fours a day at 300 words per minute.  Otherwise, ignorance of the law should be an excuse.  No one can read it all.<br/><br/>That would put a cap on all laws at 100,000,000 words.  And that in itself is a lot.<br/><br/>For any new law proposed, the government should simplify or eliminate old laws to stay under the limit.</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_3600" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_3600', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2237&topicID=3600')">Comments (0)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_3600"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2237">Making Government Operations More Open</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_3600"></div>
