<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_3558"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3558-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3558">OUO and related "classifications"&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/6746-4049">farseer2002</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">4 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">ALL federal documents, whether written by the government or by contractors working for the government should be born unclassified (with rare and specific exceptions - e.g. nuclear weapons design).<br/><br/>By executive order - eliminate ALL administrative classifications not called out by law.  If a document is classified or restricted or contains such information it should be appropriately classified and controlled.  Official Use Only (OUO) is an administrative classification used by the government to avoid releasing documents despite lacking any real classification.  Eliminate OUO entirely.<br/></div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_3558" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_3558', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2237&topicID=3558')">Comments (0)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_3558"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2237">Making Government Operations More Open</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_3558"></div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr id="row_3556">
<td width="120" align="center" valign="top" style="padding-left:10px;">
<div id="DiscussionTopicVote_3556">
